Privacy Policy
ChessClock+ is a free app created and released by independent developer Brad Bambara. This app is provided by Brad Bambara at no cost and is intended for use as is.
This page is used to inform visitors of policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal information of anyone deciding to use this app.
Log Data
The only data collection that may occur during the use of the ChessClock+ app is telemetric data collected by the underlying iOS operating system. This data is only viewable by me in aggregate, and does not describe any specific user in detail. The app does not use any third-party libraries or products which might collect personal information or data.
Information Collection and Use
ChessClock+ app stores only data describing clock settings and other user preferences. The app stores this data locally on the device and does not send data over the internet, or share data with any other party.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
I may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. I will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
This policy is effective as of 2023-02-07
Contact
If you have any questions or suggestions about my Privacy Policy, you can contact me
